<subSubSection id="B6A6AFB4AE4ACF29FF79FA8BFBAEF8BE" pageId="21" pageNumber="271" type="description">
<paragraph id="FE03FC3FAE4ACF29FF79FA8BFE80FAC2" blockId="21.[151,970,1338,1401]" box="[151,311,1375,1401]" pageId="21" pageNumber="271">
<figureCitation id="6687E0BAAE4ACF29FF79FA8BFE80FAC2" box="[151,311,1375,1401]" captionStart="FIGURES 228–247" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1860,1884]" captionTargetBox="[157,1425,191,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-16@22.[151,1436,181,1836]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 228–247. Male genitalia. 228–233―Anaceratagallia (Anaceratagallia) aciculata, 234–236―A. (A.) kungradica, 237–238―A. (A.) aciculata sensu Khatri et al., 2010, 239–240―A. (A.) seriphidii, holotype, 241–245―A. (A.) acuteangulata, 246–247―A. (Oedicora) kerzhneri. 228, 230, 232, 234, 237, 239, 241–242, 246―penis, lateral view, 229, 231, 233, 235–236, 240, 243–245―male anal collar appendage, 238―end of pygofer lobe and male anal collar appendage, 247―end of pygofer lobe. 234–236―after Dubovsky (1967), 237–238―after Khatri et al. (2010)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4398510" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4398510/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="271">Figs. 239–240</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FE03FC3FAE4ACF29FF79FA72FB5BF996" blockId="21.[151,1437,1446,1977]" pageId="21" pageNumber="271">
<emphasis id="CCC8202DAE4ACF29FF79FA72FE9EFA7B" bold="true" box="[151,297,1446,1472]" pageId="21" pageNumber="271">Description.</emphasis>
Only the 
<typeStatus id="2107429DAE4ACF29FE7AFA73FE4EFA7A" box="[404,505,1447,1473]" pageId="21" pageNumber="271">holotype</typeStatus>
, male, with the labels “ 
<quantity id="394451DAAE4ACF29FD1BFA73FC8AFA7A" box="[757,829,1447,1473]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="21" pageNumber="271" unit="km" value="40.0">40 km</quantity>
South of Zhana-Arka St.[Railway Station], Karaganda Obl[ast] [
<collectingCountry id="86ABBCAFAE4ACF29FEEFFA1EFE3AFA5E" box="[257,397,1482,1509]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="21" pageNumber="271">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
]. 16.IX.[19]60. Emelyanov” (handwritten, in Russian, our comments in square brackets) and “ 
<typeStatus id="2107429DAE4ACF29FF4FFA3BFEAEF9B2" box="[161,281,1519,1545]" pageId="21" pageNumber="271">Holotypus</typeStatus>
<taxonomicName id="39BC87BCAE4ACF29FEF1FA3BFDDBF9B2" authority="Emelyanov" authorityName="Emelyanov" box="[287,620,1519,1545]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Agallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="271" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="seriphidii">
<emphasis id="CCC8202DAE4ACF29FEF1FA3BFE54F9B2" box="[287,483,1519,1545]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="271">Agallia seriphidii</emphasis>
Emelyanov
</taxonomicName>
” (on red paper, first word printed, species name and author handwritten), deposited in Zoological Institute of Russian Academy of Sciences, St. Petersburg was investigated.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FE03FC3FAE4ACF29FF29F9E3FC75F9CE" blockId="21.[151,1437,1446,1977]" pageId="21" pageNumber="271">
Penis in side view with serrated ventral crest in basal half and slightly concave dorsal margin (
<figureCitation id="6687E0BAAE4ACF29FB02F9E3FAF8F9EA" box="[1260,1359,1591,1617]" captionStart="FIGURES 228–247" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1860,1884]" captionTargetBox="[157,1425,191,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-16@22.[151,1436,181,1836]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 228–247. Male genitalia. 228–233―Anaceratagallia (Anaceratagallia) aciculata, 234–236―A. (A.) kungradica, 237–238―A. (A.) aciculata sensu Khatri et al., 2010, 239–240―A. (A.) seriphidii, holotype, 241–245―A. (A.) acuteangulata, 246–247―A. (Oedicora) kerzhneri. 228, 230, 232, 234, 237, 239, 241–242, 246―penis, lateral view, 229, 231, 233, 235–236, 240, 243–245―male anal collar appendage, 238―end of pygofer lobe and male anal collar appendage, 247―end of pygofer lobe. 234–236―after Dubovsky (1967), 237–238―after Khatri et al. (2010)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4398510" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4398510/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="271">Fig. 239</figureCitation>
). Male anal collar appendage narrow, bent upwards, with pointed tip (
<figureCitation id="6687E0BAAE4ACF29FCBCF98FFC01F9CE" box="[850,950,1627,1653]" captionStart="FIGURES 228–247" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1860,1884]" captionTargetBox="[157,1425,191,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-16@22.[151,1436,181,1836]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 228–247. Male genitalia. 228–233―Anaceratagallia (Anaceratagallia) aciculata, 234–236―A. (A.) kungradica, 237–238―A. (A.) aciculata sensu Khatri et al., 2010, 239–240―A. (A.) seriphidii, holotype, 241–245―A. (A.) acuteangulata, 246–247―A. (Oedicora) kerzhneri. 228, 230, 232, 234, 237, 239, 241–242, 246―penis, lateral view, 229, 231, 233, 235–236, 240, 243–245―male anal collar appendage, 238―end of pygofer lobe and male anal collar appendage, 247―end of pygofer lobe. 234–236―after Dubovsky (1967), 237–238―after Khatri et al. (2010)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4398510" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4398510/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="271">Fig. 240</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FE03FC3FAE4ACF29FF29F9ABFBAEF8BE" blockId="21.[151,1437,1446,1977]" pageId="21" pageNumber="271">
The genital block was dissected into separate parts; the part that we consider to be male anal collar appendage is shown on 
<figureCitation id="6687E0BAAE4ACF29FEC5F977FE39F906" box="[299,398,1699,1725]" captionStart="FIGURES 228–247" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1860,1884]" captionTargetBox="[157,1425,191,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-16@22.[151,1436,181,1836]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 228–247. Male genitalia. 228–233―Anaceratagallia (Anaceratagallia) aciculata, 234–236―A. (A.) kungradica, 237–238―A. (A.) aciculata sensu Khatri et al., 2010, 239–240―A. (A.) seriphidii, holotype, 241–245―A. (A.) acuteangulata, 246–247―A. (Oedicora) kerzhneri. 228, 230, 232, 234, 237, 239, 241–242, 246―penis, lateral view, 229, 231, 233, 235–236, 240, 243–245―male anal collar appendage, 238―end of pygofer lobe and male anal collar appendage, 247―end of pygofer lobe. 234–236―after Dubovsky (1967), 237–238―after Khatri et al. (2010)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4398510" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4398510/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="271">Fig. 240</figureCitation>
. The shape of anal collar appendage on the drawing in the original description is different although the shape of the penis is exactly the same, as on 
<figureCitation id="6687E0BAAE4ACF29FCCEF913FC36F95A" box="[800,897,1735,1761]" captionStart="FIGURES 228–247" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1860,1884]" captionTargetBox="[157,1425,191,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-16@22.[151,1436,181,1836]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 228–247. Male genitalia. 228–233―Anaceratagallia (Anaceratagallia) aciculata, 234–236―A. (A.) kungradica, 237–238―A. (A.) aciculata sensu Khatri et al., 2010, 239–240―A. (A.) seriphidii, holotype, 241–245―A. (A.) acuteangulata, 246–247―A. (Oedicora) kerzhneri. 228, 230, 232, 234, 237, 239, 241–242, 246―penis, lateral view, 229, 231, 233, 235–236, 240, 243–245―male anal collar appendage, 238―end of pygofer lobe and male anal collar appendage, 247―end of pygofer lobe. 234–236―after Dubovsky (1967), 237–238―after Khatri et al. (2010)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4398510" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4398510/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="271">Fig. 239</figureCitation>
. Drawings of this species by 
<bibRefCitation id="9A2D81CEAE4ACF29FB24F913FACEF95A" author="Mityaev, I. D." box="[1226,1401,1735,1761]" pageId="21" pageNumber="271" refId="ref13797" refString="Mityaev, I. D. (1971) Cicadinea of Kazakhstan. Keys for identification of species. &quot; Nauka &quot; Publ., Alma-Ata, 211 pp. [in Russian]" type="book" year="1971">Mityaev (1971)</bibRefCitation>
do not clarify the situation, since they are reproduced from the original description.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B6A6AFB4AE4ACF29FF29F8DAFE58F82E" pageId="21" pageNumber="271" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="FE03FC3FAE4ACF29FF29F8DAFB90F8CA" blockId="21.[151,1437,1446,1977]" pageId="21" pageNumber="271">
<emphasis id="CCC8202DAE4ACF29FF29F8DAFE90F893" bold="true" box="[199,295,1806,1832]" pageId="21" pageNumber="271">Biology.</emphasis>
On 
<taxonomicName id="39BC87BCAE4ACF29FEB9F8DBFE73F892" box="[343,452,1807,1833]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Artemisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="21" pageNumber="271" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CCC8202DAE4ACF29FEB9F8DBFE73F892" box="[343,452,1807,1833]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="271">Artemisia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(subg. 
<emphasis id="CCC8202DAE4ACF29FDF6F8DBFD16F892" box="[536,673,1807,1833]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="271">Seriphidium</emphasis>
). Hibernates at the egg stage and reaches 3 
<superScript id="09C95177AE4ACF29FB68F8DAFB14F892" attach="none" box="[1158,1187,1806,1833]" fontSize="6" pageId="21" pageNumber="271">rd–</superScript>
4 
<superScript id="09C95177AE4ACF29FB5EF8DAFB0AF8A7" attach="left" box="[1200,1213,1806,1820]" fontSize="6" pageId="21" pageNumber="271">th</superScript>
instar by the end of June. In July–August, when host plants wither, the development of nymphs temporarily stops and resumes in the end of August. Adult specimens emerge in September (Emelyanov, pers. comm.).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FE03FC3FAE4ACF29FF29F8AEFE58F82E" blockId="21.[151,1437,1446,1977]" box="[199,495,1914,1941]" pageId="21" pageNumber="271">
<emphasis id="CCC8202DAE4ACF29FF29F8AEFEC5F82F" bold="true" box="[199,370,1914,1940]" pageId="21" pageNumber="271">Calling signal.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
